<br>
 <p>=DC=Turin Turambar, Ecthelion, and Gothmog (Viking, Knight, Pirate)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uraycoom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raycoom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 10:46:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> I read a bit of that thread, and my answer would be yes and no hehe.<br>
<br>
The no part comes from the fact that this server is much smaller, so do to raw numbers, arguements about whos going to have access to a High end encounter will likely be few and far between. <br>
<br>
The yes part comes from me thinking the servers &quot;uber guilds&quot; will be/are totally ooc. Will they drop to the point of common talk of &quot;port b*tches&quot; &quot;rezz hoes&quot; and a few other comments I saw on that thread I won't even mention, I hope not, and if they do I certainly hope its kept to /tell and /gu.<br>
<br>
I think there is hope for a &quot;in character&quot; uber guild ( or should I say guild a great power instead &lt;g&gt; ) or 2 here, it simply requires people to stay in character, keep playing the game, and not delete their characters.... many people, roleplayers and ooc-gamers alike, seem to think this is impossible, I however do not. We'll see<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udreks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 11:47:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> I tend to think not.<br>
<br>
I coached kids sports for a good 15 years. There are alot of good kids out there, but the phrases I saw, and the attitudes are those of  the type that cannot contend with their age group on even terms. They have no power so they simply don't understand concepts that &quot;tough&quot;, &quot;cool&quot; kids do. <br>
<br>
They get in a situation where they can attain power, and they wield it like a child with his daddies gun. The computer gives these types a perfect environment to do so with no checks or balances beyond the GMs. The language is symptomatic of that dysfunction  <br>
<br>
<br>
Those same types are simply not drawn to a server where they can't twink, PL, farm etc. Luckily, In the effort to &quot;prove&quot; how utterly kewl they are, we are thought of collectively as dweebs, geeks etc. Not of interest except to laugh at. <br>
<br>
Beyond that, and because of the special nature of this server, I would hope the GM staff on this server would stand with the majority so that the other guilds would not have to resort to flooding zones, causing trains, huge death tolls, and creating a situation where no one would win until the kiddies realized that the behavior would not be tolerate. <br>
<br>
Over all though, I just don't think this server is conducive to that type of environment.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usoneldarblackrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soneldar Blackrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 1:06:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> That is going to be the downfall of Druzzil Ro, and we get to learn from their mistake. <p>Soneldar Blackrose<br>
