<br>
Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroawen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roawen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 2:47:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> That happens on every single server. There is always a bunch of guilds who get together and set up rotations for uberzone_01 and there is always one guild who, for whatever reason, thinks the rotation sucks and go in and mess it all up. Its part of EQ. There's no getting around it. As far as that happening on FV, I dont know. Im sure eventually it will happen as the server ages, but right now I dont think there are enough people period to clear NToV much less dispute who's turn it is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umollycat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mollycat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 12:05:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this the future of FV?</span><hr size=1> Doesn't happen on every server, but consider this - on the servers I've been on where there was NO rotation there was a hell of a lot more respect and cooperation between guilds than ones that set up a rotation.<br>
<br>
The guilds went on a &quot;get there first&quot; system. If your guild had the moxy to go at a monster first, then you took it.<br>
<br>
It really rewarded guilds who had what it took to get organized FAST, and punished guilds who couldn't organize themselves out of a paper bag.<br>
<br>
It will never be an issue on FV though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 8:53:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I suspect ..</span><hr size=1> .. FV will be a hell of a lot like my old server on this.  Lots of multi-guild or cross-guild raids until the server is very old indeed and one guild becomes strong enough to &quot;solo&quot; one of the bigger creatures.<br>
<br>
It's going to be fun to see evils and good cooperating here on FV on the big stuff.  That's the only way the bigger things will be able to be done for a long while.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 299<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 6:37:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I suspect ..</span><hr size=1> It's going to be fun to see evils and good cooperating here on FV on the big stuff. That's the only way the bigger things will be able to be done for a long while.<br>
