<br>
I like the idea of good and evil putting their differences aside to destroy bigger foes 1 or 2 nights a week. It doesn't mean both sides love each other, and it doesn't mean both sides won't enter a guild war with each other the very next day, and it certainly doesn't mean either side did anything OOC in the hole proccess. Lightin up Shin, a day where two in character guilds of good and evil, developed the power and numbers to combine strength and take down a common enemy will be a huge feat for roleplaying on this server, surely you can't be so on the RP defensive that you can't see that?<br>
<br>
Its a &quot;sad day for RP&quot; when a Uberguild of Dark elves takes down Innoruuk and shouts &quot;w00t!&quot; when he goes down heh. If combining powers with the forces of light for 1 night to take down a common enemy is against Shintous in character morales, GREAT, but don't claim that its against Roleplaying in generall.<br>
<br>
This thinking that Roleplayers have to be weak,low in level, unskilled and unorganized with no high end material goals has to stop, or RP really WILL die on this server. <br>
